{{Spanish name|Miret|Magdalena}}
'''Enrique Miret Magdalena''' (12 January 1914 – 12 October 2009) was a [[Laity|lay]] [[theologian]]<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=F1wWKJVaZeIC&pg=PA163 Encarnación, Omar G. (2008) ''Spanish Politics: Democracy After Dictatorship'', p. 163. Polity] At Google Books. Retrieved 26 May 2013.</ref> who specialised in [[ethics]] and [[sociology]]. He was professor of Ethics at [[Universidad Complutense de Madrid]].<ref>{{es icon}} [http://www.elpais.com/articulo/sociedad/Fallece/95/anos/teologo/Enrique/Miret/Magdalena/elpepusoc/20091012elpepusoc_9/Tes "Fallece a los 95 años el teólogo Enrique Miret Magdalena"] ''[[El País]]''. Retrieved 26 May 2013.</ref>

He published some 25 books and wrote for the journal ''[[Triunfo (Spain)|Triunfo]]'' for 20 years, as well as for other publications.<ref>{{es icon}} [http://www.elmundo.es/elmundo/2009/10/13/opinion/19726612.html "El último teólogo seglar"] ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]''. Retrieved 26 May 2013.</ref>

