{{Infobox Podcast |title = ''Point of Inquiry'' |image = Point of Inquiry logo.png |caption = |host = Kavin Senapathy, [[James Underdown]] |url = [http://www.pointofinquiry.org/ www.pointofinquiry.org/] |status = Weekly |began = 2005 |ended = |genre = science{{\}} news{{\}} religion |ratings = Non-explicit }}
'''''Point of Inquiry''''' is the radio show and flagship [[podcast]] of the [[Center for Inquiry|Center for Inquiry (CFI)]], "a [[think tank]] promoting science, reason, and secular values in public policy and at the grass roots".<ref>This description appears at the beginning of most episodes.</ref> Started in 2005, ''Point of Inquiry'' has consistently been ranked among the best science podcasts available in [[iTunes]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.podcastalley.com/top_podcasts.php?num=50&genre=15&year=2010&month=6|title= Top 50 Rated Podcasts 6/2010 - Society & Culture &#124; Podcast Alley|accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> It has been celebrated for its guests and for the quality of its interviews.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://blogs.discovermagazine.com/badastronomy/2009/02/17/hot-needle-of-inquiry/ | title=Hot Needle of Inquiry |publisher=Bad Astronomy at discovermagazine.com |accessdate=16 April 2009 }}</ref> Former guests include leading scientists, writers and public intellectuals such as [[Neil DeGrasse Tyson]], [[Paul Krugman]], [[Lisa Randall]], [[Brian Greene]], [[Oliver Sacks]], [[Susan Jacoby]], [[David Brin]] and [[Temple Grandin]].
==Format== <!-- Deleted image removed: [[File:POI Chris Indre CSICON.jpg|thumb|left|alt=Hosts of Point of Inquiry''[[Point of inquiry]]''.]] --> ''Point of Inquiry'' is recorded at the [[Center for Inquiry]] headquarters in [[Amherst, NY]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pointofinquiry.org/about|title=About the Program &#124; Center for Inquiry|accessdate=3 June 2010}}</ref> [[iTunes]] features over 200 free episodes of ''Point of Inquiry'', averaging 30 to 35 minutes in length, with each consisting of a long form interview with a high-profile guest from the worlds of [[scientific skepticism]], [[science]], [[academia]], and [[philosophy]]. The show focuses on traditional topics in scientific skepticism, such as [[psychic]] investigations, [[alternative medicine]], alleged [[extraterrestrial life|extraterrestrial]] visitations, ghosts, and [[cryptozoology]]. It also covers current events and public policy. The inaugural episode in December, 2005 featured an interview with CFI founder [[Paul Kurtz]], who spoke about the incompatibility of science and religion.<ref name="Kurtz">{{cite web | url=http://www.pointofinquiry.org/paul_kurtz_science_and_religion_are_they_compatible/ | title=Paul Kurtz - Science and Religion - Are They Compatible? | publisher=[[Center for Inquiry]] | work=Point of Inquiry Podcast | date=11 December 2005 | accessdate=17 January 2014 | last=Grothe|first=DJ}}</ref>
In July 2012, ''Point of Inquiry'' produced their first video episode featuring Michael De Dora, Ed Brayton, [[Jessica Ahlquist]], and [[Jamie Kilstein]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FgXJT8v4HhY&feature=share&list=UUp7LPFmh6pyFpWQY6htER3A| title= Point of Inquiry In Studio: Chris Mooney Talks to Jamie Kilstein, Ed Brayton, and More.&#124; Center for Inquiry|accessdate=10 February 2013}}</ref>
Previously, [[Chris Mooney (journalist)|Chris Mooney]] hosted half of the shows with the balance split between the other hosts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.centerforinquiry.net/news/center_for_inquiry_announces_three_new_hosts_for_its_popular_podcast_point_/|title= Center for Inquiry Announces Three New Hosts for its Popular Podcast, ‘Point of Inquiry’ &#124; Center for Inquiry|accessdate=14 February 2010}}</ref>
17 October 2013 Center for Inquiry announced the "new team who will take ''Point of Inquiry'' into its next exciting phase", Lindsay Beyerstein, Josh Zepps and producer Joshua Billingsley.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Wait is Over: CFI Unveils New ‘Point of Inquiry’ Team!|url=http://www.centerforinquiry.net/news/the_wait_is_over_cfi_unveils_new_point_of_inquiry_team/|publisher=Center for Inquiry|accessdate=2013-10-17}}</ref>
On June 2, 2017, Point of Inquiry released its first episode with new host Paul Fidalgo. New hosts Kavin Senapathy and [[James Underdown]] were announced on October 15, 2018, the show is produced by CFI digital marketing strategist, Michael Powell.<ref>{{cite web |title=POINT OF INQUIRY PODCAST ANNOUNCES NEW CO-HOSTS KAVIN SENAPATHY AND JAMES UNDERDOWN |url=https://centerforinquiry.org/news/point-of-inquiry-announces-new-hosts/ |website=CFI |publisher=Center for Inquiry |accessdate=15 October 2018}}</ref>
